<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 26 at 2:47PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Charlotte
County through 315 PM EDT...
At 247 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Phenix, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Charlotte Court House...
Phenix...
Drakes Branch...
Madisonville...
Abilene...
Cullen...
and Aspen.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
